 FORMER champions Imo Grasshoppers of Owerri defeated Benue Queens 28-16 in the on-going Prudent Energy Handball League at the MKO Abiola Stadium, Abuja. The Benue team gave their best but the final outcome was not in doubt as the Grasshoppers coasted home to victory as they confined  the new entrant to another defeat. In  the other games, Kada Queens lost to Safety Babes 20 – 25, Plateau Peacocks defeated Defender Babes 18 -15, while  Rima Strikers beat Confluence Stars 32–27. Technical Director of the Handball Federation of Nigeria, Ferdinand Emeana,  is excited  over the emergence of new players while commending the teams  for their industry on the court. He said: “The competition has been going on well, hitch-free and very exciting. The teams are doing their best and no team is a push over from what I have seen here. He further  said the emergence of Kwara Adorable and the Benue Queens has given hope for the women’s game: “I must say that there is hope for the female game with what I have seen at the championship. The Kwara and Benue teams have young players who can form the bulk of the national team in future.” 